==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weakly
<hw>Weak"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a weak manner; with little
strength or vigor; feebly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weakly</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Weakly
<hw>Weak"ly</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Weaklier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Weakliest</adjf>.]</amorph> <def>Not strong of constitution;
infirm; feeble; <as>as, a <ex>weakly</ex> woman; a man of a
<ex>weakly</ex> constitution.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weak-minded</ent>⟦br⟧
